The paper deals with the average case complexity of constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) and the value of mathematical relaxations such as linear and semidefinite programs for CSPs. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of random subsampling of variables in CSPs, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also possible sub-categories. The paper also discusses the Lasserre hierarchy and unique games conjecture, indicating that cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
